longest_rain.status: Today, one rain storm lasted for 22.9 hours (ranking 5th for longest storm from our records).  It accumulated 7.68mm of rain and it fell at 4.1mm per hour at times.  Rain fell for 37.2 hours on 04 January 2025 creating a new record that still lasts.  The storm produced a total of 36.8mm with a maximum intensity of 4.6mm per hour.
